.TH MPD-NOTIFY "1" "December 2025" "mpd-notify 202208131219-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mpd-notify \- MPD notification daemon script
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mpd-notify
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mpd-notify
is a notification daemon for MPD (Music Player Daemon) that displays desktop notifications when the currently playing song changes. It monitors MPD for track changes and sends notifications with song information.
.PP
The script can run as a background daemon and integrates with the system's notification service to display track information including artist, album, and song title.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B start
Start the notification daemon
.TP
.B stop
Stop the notification daemon
.TP
.B restart
Restart the notification daemon
.TP
.B status
Display current daemon status (running/stopped)
.TP
.B toggle
Toggle the daemon on/off
.TP
.B run
Run the notification service in the foreground
.TP
.B enable
Enable the service to start automatically
.TP
.B disable
Disable automatic startup
.TP
.B term
Run in a terminal window
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available commands
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B mpd-notify start
Start the MPD notification daemon
.TP
.B mpd-notify status
Check if the daemon is running
.TP
.B mpd-notify toggle
Toggle the daemon on or off
.TP
.B mpd-notify enable
Enable autostart for the notification daemon
